#: ../../G/grue.rst:5
msgid "grue"
msgstr "grue"

#: ../../G/grue.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../G/grue.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from archaic English verb for shudder, as with fear] The grue was "
"originated in the game :ref:`Zork` (Dave Lebling took the name from Jack "
"Vance's *Dying Earth* fantasies) and used in several other :ref:`Infocom` "
"games as a hint that you should perhaps look for a lamp, torch or some type "
"of light source. Wandering into a dark area would cause the game to prompt "
"you, \"It is very dark. If you continue you are likely to be eaten by a "
"grue.\" If you failed to locate a light source within the next couple of "
"moves this would indeed be the case."
msgstr ""
"[震えるという意味の古い英語の動詞より、恐怖などで] grueはゲーム\\ :ref:`Zork`\\ で生まれ(Dave LeblingがJack "
"Vanceの *Dying Earth* ファンタジーから名前を取った)、いくつかの他の\\ :ref:`Infocom`\\ "
"のゲームで、ランプ、たいまつ、あるいは何らかの光源を探したほうがよいというヒントとして使われた。暗い場所に迷い込むと、ゲームはこう促した。「とても暗い。先に進めば、grueに食われる可能性が高い。」次の数手のうちに光源を見つけられなければ、実際にそうなった。"

#: ../../G/grue.rst:14
msgid ""
"The grue, according to scholars of the Great Underground Empire, is a "
"sinister, lurking presence in the dark places of the earth. Its favorite "
"diet is either adventurers or enchanters, but its insatiable appetite is "
"tempered by its extreme fear of light. No grues have ever been seen by the "
"light of day, and only a few have been observed in their underground lairs. "
"Of those who have seen grues, few have survived their fearsome jaws to tell "
"the tale. Grues have sickly glowing fur, fish-mouthed faces, sharp claws and"
" fangs, and an uncontrollable tendency to slaver and gurgle. They are "
"certainly the most evil-tempered of all creatures; to say they are touchy is"
" a dangerous understatement. \"Sour as a grue\" is a common expression, even"
" among grues themselves."
msgstr ""
"大地下帝国の学者によれば、grueは地中の暗い場所に潜む不吉な存在である。その好物は冒険者か魔法使いだが、その飽くなき食欲は光への極端な恐怖によって抑えられている。grueが昼の光のもとで見られたことは一度もなく、地下の隠れ家で観察されたものもほんのわずかである。grueを見た者のうち、その恐ろしい顎を生き延びて語ることのできた者はわずかである。grueは病的に光る毛、魚のような口の顔、鋭い爪と牙を持ち、よだれを垂らしてゴボゴボ鳴らす抑えがたい傾向がある。あらゆる生き物の中で最も気性が悪いのは確かである。彼らが怒りっぽいと言うのは危険な控えめな表現である。「grueのように不機嫌」はgrue自身の間でさえ一般的な表現である。"

#: ../../G/grue.rst:22
msgid "All this folklore is widely known among hackers."
msgstr "このフォークロアはすべてハッカーの間で広く知られている。"
